---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Container from "../components/ui/Container.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about Open Waters and our mission to build better tools for understanding and navigating the sea."
>
  <Container class="py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-8 text-center">About Open Waters</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-navy-600">Hi there!</p>

        <p>
          I'm Brandon, and I started Open Water Software as a home for various
          projects related to marine software and data. My hope is that it grows
          into a community where mariners, developers, and ocean enthusiasts can
          come together to build better tools for understanding and navigating
          the sea.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12">"Open" as in "The Ocean"</h2>

        <p>
          The ocean is a commons. We all depend on it, and we are all
          responsible for preserving it. Centuries of mariners, hydrographers,
          scientists, and engineers chose to share what they learned about the
          sea, and we've all benefited.
        </p>

        <p>
          Open source software works the same way. By freely sharing what we
          build—and collaborating openly—we create tools that are better, more
          reliable, and more useful to everyone. Open Water Software is
          committed to producing open source tools and data.
        </p>

        <div
          class="my-8 rounded-r-lg border-l-4 border-ocean-600 bg-ocean-50 p-6"
        >
          <p class="mb-4 font-medium text-navy-900">
            If you want to learn more or talk about ways to contribute, get in
            touch.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-0">
            Cheers!<br />
            <strong>Brandon Keepers</strong><br />
            <span class="text-navy-600"
              >Founder of Open Water Software, LLC</span
            >
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12">Our Projects</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-ocean-400 pl-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Tide Predictions</h3>
            <p class="mb-2">
              Accurate tide predictions powered by our Neaps engine, with
              comprehensive data from thousands of reference and subordinate
              stations worldwide.
            </p>
            <a
              href="/tides"
              class="font-medium text-ocean-600 hover:text-ocean-700"
            >
              Learn more about tides →
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-ocean-400 pl-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Crowd Depth</h3>
            <p class="mb-2">
              Help improve nautical charts by sharing depth data from your
              vessel. Our Signal K plugin makes it easy to contribute to
              crowd-sourced bathymetry programs.
            </p>
            <a
              href="/bathymetry"
              class="font-medium text-ocean-600 hover:text-ocean-700"
            >
              Learn more about bathymetry →
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-ocean-400 pl-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Developer API</h3>
            <p class="mb-2">
              Access our marine data programmatically through well-documented
              APIs. Build your own tools and applications using our open data.
            </p>
            <a
              href="/api"
              class="font-medium text-ocean-600 hover:text-ocean-700"
            >
              View API documentation →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12">Get Involved</h2>

        <p>
          We welcome contributions from anyone interested in marine software and
          data. Whether you're a developer, a mariner with domain knowledge, or
          someone who loves the ocean, there's a place for you in our community.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/openwatersio"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="btn btn-primary"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:github" class="size-6" />
            View on GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="mailto:info@openwaters.io" class="btn btn-secondary">
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: theme("colors.navy.800");
  }

  .prose h2 {
    color: theme("colors.navy.900");
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    color: theme("colors.navy.900");
  }

  .prose a {
    color: theme("colors.ocean.600");
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    color: theme("colors.ocean.700");
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
</style>
